{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":false,"flaws":{},"title":"JSON.parse()","mdn_url":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON/parse","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects\">Standard-Objekte</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON\"><code>JSON</code></a></strong></li><li data-default-state=\"open\"><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><em><code>JSON.parse()</code></em></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON/stringify\"><code>JSON.stringify()</code></a></li></ol></li><li><strong>Vererbung:</strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object\"><code>Object</code></a></strong></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Eigenschaften</strong></a><ol><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/constructor\"><code>Object.prototype.constructor</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/proto\"><code>Object.prototype.__proto__</code></a></li></ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p>Die Methode&nbsp;<strong><code>JSON.parse()</code></strong> erzeugt aus einem JSON-formatierten Text ein entsprechendes Javascript-Objekt. Der optionale <strong>reviver</strong>-Parameter kann die Umwandlung im Detail beeinflussen.</p>\n\n<div id=\"sect2\"><iframe class=\"interactive\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/js/json-parse.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"syntaxbox notranslate\">JSON.parse(<var>text</var>[, <var>reviver</var>])</pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameter","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"text\"><code>text</code></dt>\n <dd>JSON-formatierter Text, der eingelesen werden soll. Siehe <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON\"><code>JSON</code></a> für eine Beschreibung der JavaScript Objekt Notation.</dd>\n <dt id=\"reviver\"><code>reviver</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n <dd>\n <p><span id=\"result_box\" lang=\"de\"><span>Wenn es sich um eine Funktion handelt, schreibt diese vor, wie der ursprünglich vom Parsen erzeugte Wert transformiert wird, bevor er zurückgegeben wird.</span></span></p>\n </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"returns","title":"Rückgabewert","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Die Funktion gibt das aus <code>text</code> erzeugte <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object\"><code>Object</code></a> zurück.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"throws","title":"Ausnahmen","isH3":true,"content":"<p><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/SyntaxError\"><code>SyntaxError</code></a>, falls <code>text</code> kein gültiges JSON enthält.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Beispiele","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_using_json.parse","title":"<code>JSON.parse()</code> verwenden","isH3":true,"content":"<pre class=\"notranslate\">JSON.parse('{}');              // {}\nJSON.parse('true');            // true\nJSON.parse('\"foo\"');           // \"foo\"\nJSON.parse('[1, 5, \"false\"]'); // [1, 5, \"false\"]\nJSON.parse('null');            // null\n</pre>","titleAsText":"JSON.parse() verwenden"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_using_the_reviver_parameter","title":"Verwendung des <code>reviver</code>-Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Wenn <code>reviver</code> spezifiziert ist, wird der vom Parser berechnete Wert vor der Rückgabe Transformiert. Insbesondere der berechnete Wert und alle seine EIgenschaften (beginnend mit dem am tiefsten geschachtelten Eigenschaft bis hin zum originalen Wert selbst) werden separat mit dem <code>reviver</code> Ausgeführt.<span id=\"result_box\" lang=\"de\"><span> Dann wird sie aufgerufen, wobei das Objekt, das die Eigenschaft enthält, als <code>this</code> und der Eigenschaftsname als Zeichenfolge und der Eigenschaftswert als Argumente verarbeitet werden.</span></span> Wenn <code>reviver</code> <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/undefined\"><code>undefined</code></a>&nbsp;zurück gibt (oder keinen Wert zurück gibt, wenn zum Beispiel die Ausführung der Funktion fehlschlägt), wird die Eigenschaft aus dem Ergebnis entfernt. Anderenfalls wird dessen Wert in den Rückgabewert neu definiert.</p>\n\n<p>Falls <code>reviver</code> nur einige Werte ändert, muss sichergestellt sein, dass die unveränderten Werte auch zurückgegeben werden, ansonsten werden diese Werte aus dem Ergebnis gelöscht.</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token constant\">JSON</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">parse</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'{\"p\": 5}'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">key<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> value</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">typeof</span> value <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token string\">'number'</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">?</span> value <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Gibt value * 2 für Zahlen zurück.</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">:</span> value     <span class=\"token comment\">// Alle anderen Werte werden unverändert zurückgegeben.</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// { p: 10 }</span>\n\n<span class=\"token constant\">JSON</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">parse</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'{\"1\": 1, \"2\": 2, \"3\": {\"4\": 4, \"5\": {\"6\": 6}}}'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">key<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> value</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>key<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Loggt die Namen der Eigenschaften, der letzte ist \"\".</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> value<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>     <span class=\"token comment\">// Gib den unveränderten Eigenschaftenwert zurück.</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// 1</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// 2</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// 4</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// 6</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// 5</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// 3</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// \"\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>","titleAsText":"Verwendung des reviver-Parameters"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"json.parse()_erlaubt_keine_abschließenden_kommas","title":"<code>JSON.parse()</code> erlaubt keine abschließenden Kommas","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"example-bad brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">// Beides erzeugt einen Syntaxfehler</span>\n<span class=\"token constant\">JSON</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">parse</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"[1, 2, 3, 4, ]\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token constant\">JSON</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">parse</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"{ \\\"foo\\\" : 1, }\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>","titleAsText":"JSON.parse() erlaubt keine abschließenden Kommas"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"specifications","title":"Spezifikationen","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Spezifikation</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Kommentar</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/5.1/#sec-15.12.2\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 5.1 (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'JSON.parse' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>Initiale Definition. Implementiert in JavaScript 1.7.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/#sec-json.parse\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 2015 (6th Edition, ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'JSON.parse' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-json.parse\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'JSON.parse' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Lebender Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.JSON.parse","dataURL":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON/parse/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect3\">\n\n\n<p></p><p></p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON/stringify\"><code>JSON.stringify()</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Beispiele","id":"examples"},{"text":"Spezifikationen","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"Die Methode JSON.parse() erzeugt aus einem JSON-formatierten Text ein entsprechendes Javascript-Objekt. Der optionale reviver-Parameter kann die Umwandlung im Detail beeinflussen.","popularity":0.0024,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"JSON.parse()","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"JSON.parse()","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"JSON.parse()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"JSON.parse()","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"JSON.parse()","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"JSON.parse()","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"JSON.parse()","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"JSON.parse()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"JSON.parse()","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/json/parse","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/json/parse/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/de/docs/Web","title":"Webtechnologien für Entwickler"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript","title":"JavaScript"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference","title":"JavaScript-Referenz"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects","title":"Globale Objekte"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON","title":"JSON"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON/parse","title":"JSON.parse()"}],"pageTitle":"JSON.parse() - JavaScript | MDN","noIndexing":false}}